    <h1>Employment Opportunities</h1>
        <p>We provide a challenging and exciting work environment. We have a very strong work ethic but realize that because you spend one third of your day at work, you will not be successful if you do not enjoy your work. To that end, we provide a casual work environment where people are encouraged to reach their full potential. We offer competitive wages and benefits: Health Insurance, Vacation, Semi-flexible hours, Training, and Company paid outings.</p>
        <p>We are continually accepting resumes for the following positions. Check back periodically for any immediate openings.</p>
    
    <h2 class="big">Immediate Openings:</h2>
    <h3 style="margin-top: 10px;">Sales Agents</h3>
        <p>Work as many or as little hours as you like! This is an ideal position to supplement your existing income.</p>
        <p>Qualifications include: Understanding of software, computer hardware and networking concepts. Friendly, outgoing personality. Strong ability to make new contacts and close sales.  Excellent written skills. Some experience selling software, hardware, or computer related services is desirable.</p>
        <p>Sales Agents are paid a generous commission.</p>
    
    <h2 class="big">Ongoing Recruitment:</h2> 
    <h3 style="margin-top: 10px;">Senior Programmers</h3>
        <p>Responsibilities include leading software development projects and writing code. Qualifications include four year computer science degree with experience. Must be extremely knowledgeable with VB.NET and client/server databases such as SQL Server or Oracle. Proven ability to lead and train other programmers and lead a project from design to implementation. Must have experience creating both web-based and desktop applications.</p>
    
    <h3>Junior Programmers </h3>
        <p>Responsibilities include creating forms for graphical user interfaces, reports, database design, installation programs, help files and documentation. Qualifications include four year computer science degree or two year computer science degree with some experience. Must be knowledgeable with VB.NET and databases such as Access or SQL Server. Knowledge with web page design is desirable.</p>
    
    <h3>Computer/Network Technicians </h3>
        <p>Responsibilities include on-site setup and maintenance of client computers and networks. Qualifications include two year computer related degree. Must be knowledgeable with PC repair, Windows operating systems including server editions, network protocols and network hardware. Some programming knowledge desirable. Experience is desirable. A+ certification and Microsoft Certified Professional (working toward MCSE) is desirable.</p>
        
    <h3>Internships</h3>
        <p>Internships are available for all of the above positions. We immerse our interns in all aspects of our business. You won't be a doughnut gopher here! In fact, many of our interns become full-time employees.</p>
        <p>Qualifications include near completion of a two or four degree in an appropriate field. Some experience relative to the position is desirable.</p>
      
    <h2 class="big">Mail your resume to: </h2>
    <p>Century Software Group, LLC<br />
        9 Carriage Drive<br />
        East Greenbush, NY 12061<br />
        <br />
        Indicate that a resume is enclosed on the envelope. <br />
        <br />
        Or <a href="javascript://" onclick="sendmail('careers','centurysoftwaregroup','com');return false">Email Us</a><br />
        
    </p>

        

        
        
        
        
